<paragraph id="5848C94E2D67FF8AFF98FF12FBC50AB5" blockId="15.[151,1436,223,391]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
This group is characterized by being slender and of medium length (
<quantity id="9F0F64AB2D67FF8AFC80FF12FC520BC5" box="[911,1009,223,247]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" unit="mm" value="5.0" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="4.0">4â€“6 mm</quantity>
); the pronotum is not very convex and weakly impressed medially, red, with a moderate transverse depression anterior to blue base, and with very fine prehumeral carinae parallel to and just interior to marginal carina; elytra have the apices angulate or obliquely truncate, the posterior 
<number id="EE3FDB692D67FF8AFE6BFE81FED10A56" box="[356,370,332,356]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="2.0">2</number>
/ 
<number id="EE3FDB692D67FF8AFE73FE81FE2B0A56" box="[380,392,332,356]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="3.0">3</number>
is covered uniformly with more or less dense golden setae, the anterior margin of golden area prolonged medially along suture interior to the costae, beyond the dark lateral margins.
</paragraph>
